<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-636-191  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 636 191.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 26 1990 v7 n48 p9(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI reorganization bodes well for users. (MCI CommunicationsCorp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communication Corp, like AT and T and US Sprint CommunicationsCo, is in the process of reorganizing in order to respond fasterto user demands and improve operating efficiencies.andP;  All threecarriers are eliminating redundant divisional operations that wereoriginally set up to parallel the regional Bell holding companies'geographic layout.andP;  This action allows for cost reductions andmore funding for marketing and research.andP;  Management is alsobecoming centralized while account representatives are being keptin the field near customer sites.andP;  Some observers feel that AT andT has been renewing efforts to halt its slipping market share andthis has forced US Sprint and MCI to respond.andP;  MCI is planning tofold its seven regional service divisions into three new groupscomprised of Business Markets, Consumer Markets and NetworkServices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Management)US Sprint Communications Co. (Management)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Management).andO;Ticker:    T; MCIC.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationTelephone CompaniesMarket ShareCentralizationBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>